<TEXT type="str">White House chief strategist Steve Bannon now reportedly has a seat on the… White House chief strategist Steve Bannon now reportedly has a seat on the National Security Council.

President Trump signed an executive order Saturday reshuffling the NSC, according to the Washington Post.

With Bannon’s addition to the NSC, the Director of National Intelligence and the chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff will only sit on the council when “issues pertaining to their responsibilities and expertise are to be discussed,” the Washington Post reported.

